agents.prompt_template:
Analyze the raw idea and produce a structured feature description.

Raw idea: {{feature_description}}

Output to: {{output_path}}/product-discovery.json

Analyze the feature request and produce a PRD following the StageOutput schema. Feature: {{feature_description}}

Context files:
{{context_files}}

Output to: {{output_path}}/requirements.json

Design database schema changes for:

PRD: {{S1_output}}

Existing tables: {{table_list}}

Output to: {{output_path}}/database-design.json

Design the complete UI for this feature.

PRD: {{S1_output}}
Architecture: {{S2_output}}

Output to: {{output_path}}/ui-design.json

Write comprehensive unit tests for the implementation.

PRD acceptance criteria: {{S1_output}}
Architecture: {{S2_output}}
Implementation: {{S3_output}}

Requirements:
- Unit tests for all new methods
- 80%+ coverage target
- Test edge cases and error paths

Output to: {{output_path}}/testing.json

Write integration tests for the backend services.

Architecture: {{S2_output}}
Implementation: {{S3_output}}
Unit test results: {{S4_output}}

Requirements:
- Test API endpoint request/response
- Test Dubbo service interactions
- Test database operations with real DB
- Test MQ message handling

Output to: {{output_path}}/integration-testing.json

Write E2E tests for critical user journeys.

PRD user stories: {{S1_output}}
Frontend: {{S3b_output}}
Backend APIs: {{S3_output}}

Requirements:
- Cover all critical user flows from PRD
- Use Playwright for browser automation
- Screenshot on failure
- Test responsive layouts

Output to: {{output_path}}/e2e-testing.json

Explore the running application as a real user.

PRD user stories: {{S1_output}}
Frontend: {{S3b_output}}
Backend APIs: {{S3_output}}
App URL: {{app_url}}

Use gstack browse CLI ($B) to navigate, click, fill forms, and verify.
Do NOT write test scripts — explore interactively.

Output to: {{output_path}}/browser-qa.json

Prepare deployment for this feature.

Architecture: {{S2_output}}
Implementation: {{S3_output}}
Test results: {{S4_output}}
Review results: {{S5_output}}

Generate:
- Deployment checklist
- Rollback plan
- Monitoring alerts to add

Output to: {{output_path}}/deployment.json

Write comprehensive documentation for this feature.

PRD: {{S1_output}}
Architecture: {{S2_output}}
Implementation: {{S3_output}}
API endpoints: {{S2_output}}

Generate:
- API documentation with examples
- User guide sections
- Changelog entry
- Architecture diagram description
- Operational runbook

Output to: {{output_path}}/documentation.json

Design and analyze performance tests for this feature.

Architecture: {{S2_output}}
Implementation: {{S3_output}}
NFRs: {{S1_output}}

Generate:
- Benchmark definitions with thresholds
- Load test configuration
- Performance recommendations
- Database query analysis

Output to: {{output_path}}/performance.json

Prepare the final release decision brief for this feature.

Deployment plan: {{S6_output}}
Monitoring: {{S7_output}}
Documentation: {{S8_output}}
Performance: {{S9_output}}
Test results: {{S4_output}}
Code review: {{S5_output}}

IMPORTANT: Do NOT generate a manual verification checklist. All verification items (compile, build, smoke test, env scan, etc.) MUST be automated in pipeline stages S3-S9. The human reviewer should NEVER manually run commands.

Generate:
1. Evidence summary — auto-collected from S3-S9 outputs (test pass rates, review scores, perf benchmarks, monitoring alerts count). Show GREEN/YELLOW/RED per stage.
2. Known technical debt — list unresolved issues from S5/S9 with severity, impact, and recommended timeline to fix (v1.1/v1.2/backlog)
3. Release Notes draft — user-facing changelog with known limitations honestly declared
4. Rollback plan — trigger conditions + automated steps + estimated time
5. Deployment strategy — rolling/canary/blue-green with rationale
6. Stakeholder notifications — pre-drafted messages for dev/ops/business/CEO

The human reviewer will ONLY decide: (a) release timing, (b) risk acceptance for known debt, (c) Release Notes approval.

Output to: {{output_path}}/release.json
